[SN]TITLE[SN]
European Cross Country Championships 2016: GB team in confident mood

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Team captain Andrew Butchart hopes to help Great Britain top the medal table at the European Cross Country Championships for a 14th year in a row.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Butchart, who was sixth in the 5,000m at the Olympics, heads the men's team of six in Sardinia on Sunday.
The 25-year-old Scot said: "We are here to win as individuals and as a team. If I can get a medal for the team, I would be over the moon.
